node.text:
As Qianhai is a new city that rise from the ground, so should it’s gateway. This is the most conceptual proposal from the 4 and we were quite taken by the idea of it. A rough and natural approach rather than a shiny LED design. 

•

For the last 4 days, I posted 4 proposals for a new project of ours.

We’d love your thoughts on them and at the end of the week, tell us which one of the 4 projects you prefer.

by @studioprecht

node.text:
This option is formed by modular paddles that connect to an elevated park for people to meet, relax or just cross the street. Each paddle connect to its neighbor forming a structural system of ramps, planters, walk paths and niches.

•

For the next 4 days, I’ll post 4 proposals for a new project of ours.

We’d love your thoughts on them and at the end of the week, tell us which one of the 4 projects you prefer.

by @studioprecht

node.text:
Inspired by traditional fishing boats of the area, the gateway spans over the street to create an island of tranquility. The stepped landscape of planters, niches, stairs and ramps offers an urban plaza to the city and a stage for events to become a vivid center of life for Qianhai.

•

For the next 4 days, I’ll post 4 proposals for a new project of ours.

We’d love your thoughts on them and at the end of the week, tell us which one of the 4 projects you prefer.

by @studioprecht

@time visited us in the Austrian Mountains to talk about creativity. Here is a short film about our studio, our process, our daily inspiration and why creativity matters now more than ever.

Thanks for coming to our place @time . It was lovely hosting you and it’s such an honor to be on your radar!

#WCID #IAmCreative #WCIW #worldcreativityandinnovationday 

In partnership with @time @kia.worldwide

node.text:
During the last weeks, the messages if I sell some of our work as NFT became more and more and this increased the excitement I had already for this ‘new thing’. But after a bit of research, my excitement soured and in this video I try to speak in an honest way about the concerns and issues I have with NFT.
•
If I got any of the numbers wrong, or if you guys have contrary information or opinion, let’s discuss them. I try to educate myself as good as it gets about NFT, but behind this layer of current hype, real research is very hard to find.
•
If you have questions, remarks, contrary views or solutions, please post them here and if in future alternative platforms pop up, please let us know in the comments.
•
Here the link that I have found:
https://memoakten.medium.com/the-unreasonable-ecological-cost-of-cryptoart-2221d3eb2053

https://time.com/5947911/nft-environmental-toll/

https://www.wired.com/story/nfts-hot-effect-earth-climate/

.

node.title: NFT, the endless opportunities and why I pass on them

node.text:
I’m proud to share some updates on our ‘Flower of Qianhai’!
•
Set to become an icon of vitality and community, we designed the new gateway of Qianhai as a symbolic relationship between people and nature. 5 flowers, raised above the buzzling urban grid, provide a space to meet, relax and recreate. Differently themed gardens along a walk path connect the 2 sides of the road. An elevator in the center of one flower provides an additional access to the top.
•
Some weeks ago, I’ve shared some early sketches on the project and some of you offered comments, advice and critique. I thoroughly want to thank everyone who shared their opinion.
•
‘The flower of Qianhai’ by @studioprecht

node.text:
This is an open thought of how to design flexibility for a building differently:

The final look of this residential building could be shaped by the individual preference of each owner. 

With the current market, most of the units are sold before construction starts. A buyer can chose from a catalogue of modules like balconies, planters or clear glass. A framework within the structure allows to adapt to those individual choices.

Throughout the lifespan of the building, the facade can be changed, improved or repaired by new modules without demolishing the core-building. Updated modules can be craned in from the roof of the property allowing the building to adapt throughout decades.

Maybe this entails some thoughts that are relevant in future. To repair buildings, rather than destroying them and building new.

What are your thoughts, do you see potentials to explore further? Or are there hurdles and challenges why a building system/process like this wouldn’t work?

I would value your insight!

#adaptabuilding

We are starting to develop the first farmhouse for Montreal soon. Stay tuned.

‚The Farmhouse‘ by @studioprecht

node.text:
Our design for a renovation project in the heart of a small town called Bischofshofen (the place I grew up in).
•
Instead of stacking the apartments on top of each other, we created townhouses with 2 floors and a lush rooftop garden. The ‚houses‘ are internally connected, but seem detached to the outside. This creates a neighborhood within one building and adds a lively contribution to the center of the town.
•
‚Pferdeschmiede‘ by @studioprecht
